comments: Towns (MIN) and Sampson (IND) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Sampson (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Rubio's (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
A. Holiday (IND) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Sampson (IND) cleanly blocks Russell's (MIN) jump shot attempt before incidental arm contact occurs.
Sampson (IND) gathers the pass on his left foot and takes two steps before attempting the layup.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in McConnell's (IND) view and gives McConnell room to avoid the contact.
McConnell (IND) turns into Rubio (MIN) and delivers contact that affects Rubio's SQBR.
Rubio (MIN) and McConnell (IND) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs before they separate.
McDaniels (MIN) rests his hands on McConnell's (IND) side during the drive and marginal contact occurs.
Holiday (IND) makes contact to Russell's (MIN) side and affects his driving shot attempt.
Rubio (MIN) has his arm across McConnell's (IND) back and marginal contact occurs as he attempts to dislodge the ball during the hand-off.
Sampson (IND) has his hand on McDaniels' (MIN) back and marginal contact occurs as the rebound occurs.
Towns (MIN) and Sampson (IND) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Towns (MIN) and Sampson (IND) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Russell (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in A. Holiday's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
McConnell (IND) makes clean contact with the ball and incidental "high-five" contact with Rubio (MIN) during the jump shot attempt.
Rubio (MIN) commits a take foul on LeVert (IND).
McDaniels (MIN) commits a take foul on LeVert (IND).
Russell (MIN) and A. Holiday (IND) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
McDaniels (MIN) engages and disengage with LeVert (IND) during the inbound.
Edwards (MIN) commits a take foul on Holiday (IND).
Sampson (IND) and Rubio (MIN) come together at the same spot during the inbound and marginal body contact occurs before they separate.
Towns (MIN) and LeVert (IND) come together at the same spot in transition and marginal body contact occurs.
